        <h2 id="upgrade-jquery">Upgrade jQuery</h2>
        <p>jQuery's current version (as of May, 2019) is 3.4.1 and face-body.com is using 1.11.2. According to <a href="https://jquery.com/upgrade-guide/3.0/">jQuery's upgrade guide</a>, we are just over the cutoff of 1.11.0 or older, and so <a href="https://github.com/jquery/jquery-migrate/#README">jQuery's migration plugin</a> should have us covered.</p>
        <p>This one's a little tricky to test, though. We might want to pick a slow sales period to do this.</p>

        <h2 id="nav-bar">Nav Bar</h2>
        <p>In addition to improving color contrast (as explained below in the <strong>Colors</strong> section), the following issues deserve remediation:</p>
          <ul class="copy-list">
            <li><strong><em>Skip to content</em></strong> button should be added. (A)<br><a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/UNDERSTANDING-WCAG20/navigation-mechanisms-skip.html">Bypass Blocks, Understanding SC 2.4.1 at w3.org</a></li>
            <li>A <em>label</em> should be added to the input field. (A)<br><a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/UNDERSTANDING-WCAG20/minimize-error-cues.html">Labels or Instructions, Understanding SC 3.3.2 at w3.org</a></li>
            <li>A <strong><em>Submit</em></strong> button should be added to the search field.(A)<br><a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/2016/NOTE-WCAG20-TECHS-20161007/H32">H32: Providing submit buttons at w3.org</a> and <a href="http://uxpamagazine.org/digital-accessibility-creating-inclusive-experiences-and-avoiding-lawsuits/">Digital Accessibility: Creating Inclusive Experiences and Avoiding Lawsuits at UXPAMagazine.org</a></li>
            <li>Focus indication should be improved. (AA)<br><a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/UNDERSTANDING-WCAG20/navigation-mechanisms-focus-visible.html">Focus Visible: Understanding SC 2.4.7 at w3.org</a></li>
            <li>Increase font size to 24px as per discussion.</li>
          </ul>

        <h2 id="homepage">Homepage</h2>

        <h3>Homepage Carousel</h3>
        <p>I wasn't able to confirm that the homepage carousel, which is part of the District Shopify theme, is accessible. I suspect it is not. Options for correcting that are:</p> 
          <ul class="copy-list">
            <li>Modifying it to add accessibility features</li>
            <li>Replacing it with an accessible carousel</li>
            <li>Deleting it</li>
          </ul>
        <p>Each solution presents its own problems, of course. Modification would be overly time-consuming. Replacing would probably take less time, but would still be around 8 to 16 hours and would not be guaranteed to be visually and functionally identical. Deleting it would probably make the most sense from a purely practical perspective, but might be unnatractive for other reasons.</p>
        <p>Here are some examples of accessible carousels:</p> 
          <ul class="copy-list">
            <li><a href="https://www.w3.org/WAI/tutorials/carousels/working-example/">Web Accessibility Tutorials: Carousels at w3.org</a></li>
            <li><a href="https://www.accessibilityoz.com/">Accessibility Oz</a></li>
          </ul>
        <p>Because text over images presents additional challenges to achieving sufficient contrast, I recommend the font colors used in the carousel be either black or white. Another option is giving text a contrast-helping background color as depicted in the w3 carousel link above.</p>

        <h3>Homepage Copy and Images</h3>
        <p>The lines of copy: "<em>NEED HELP CHOOSING YOUR NUMBING PRODUCTS? VIEW THE CHART.</em>" and "<em>INSURANCE FOR YOUR TATTOO SHOP or SALON:  CLICK HERE</em>" should be reworded, "<em>FOR HELP CHOOSING YOUR NUMBING PRODUCTS, VIEW THE CHART.</em>" and "<em>CLICK HERE FOR INSURANCE FOR YOUR TATTOO SHOP or SALON</em>" respectively.
        <p>The two images below the carousel have two links each, which is redundant. <a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/WCAG20-TECHS/H2.html">H2: Combining adjacent image and text links for the same resource at w3.org</a> (A)<br>Their structure should be modified to use only one link.</p>

        <h2 id="colors">Colors (AA)</h2>
        <p><a href="https://webaim.org/resources/contrastchecker/">Webaim Color Contrast Checker</a></p>
        <p>Colors in Shopify can mostly be controlled from within the admin panel. In some areas of the face-body.com theme, direct control has been defeated either by accident or design, but putting things right should not take more than two to four hours.</p>
        <p>Here are the areas I spotted that should be changed:</p>
          <ul class="copy-list">
            <li class="with-svg">Change highlight color from<br class="mobile-only"><em>#24A9A1/#34b0b0</em>
              <span class="inline-svg-container">
                <svg style="height:100%;" viewBox="0 0 10 10" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"> <circle fill="#24A9A1" cx="5" cy="5" r="5"/> </svg> 
                  to <em>#278282</em>
                <svg style="height:100%;" viewBox="0 0 10 10" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"> <circle fill="#278282" cx="5" cy="5" r="5"/> </svg>
              </span>
            </li>
            <li class="with-svg">Change font color from<br class="mobile-only"><em>#938c8c</em>
              <span class="inline-svg-container">
                <svg style="height:100%;" viewBox="0 0 10 10" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"> <circle fill="#938c8c " cx="5" cy="5" r="5"/> </svg> 
                to <em>#595454</em>
                <svg style="height:100%;" viewBox="0 0 10 10" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"> <circle fill="#595454" cx="5" cy="5" r="5"/> </svg> 
              </span>
            </li>
            <li>See <a href="#homepage">Homepage</a> section for additional recommendations for text in the carousels.</li>
          </ul>

        <h2 id="product-collections">Product Pages & Collection Pages</h2>
        <p>Products rendered in multiple locations throughout the site suffer from the same redundant link problem described in the <a href="#homepage">homepage</a> section, Homepage Copy &amp; Images.</p>
        <ul class="copy-list">
          <li>snippets/cart-preview.liquid</li>
          <li>snippets/product-grid-item-ac.liquid</li>
          <li>snippets/product-grid-item-related-items.liquid</li>
          <li>snippets/product-grid-item-sb.liquid</li>
          <li>snippets/product-grid-item-squeeze.liquid</li>
          <li>snippets/product-grid-item.liquid</li>
          <li>snippets/product-list-item.liquid</li>
          <li>snippets/product-redirect.liquid</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Each of these theme files will require editing.</p>

        <h2 id="circular-links">Circular Links</h2>
        <p>Some links (such as the links on the <a href="https://facebodyinc.myshopify.com/collections/basic-brow-pigments/">Basic Brow Pigments</a> page) link to themselves. These should be corrected to link to the individual product pages.</> 
